place.name: HETHEL
place.gazetteerText: HETHEL, a parish in Henstead district, Norfolk; 2½ miles S by W of Hethersett r. station, and 4 E by S of Wymondham. Post town, Hethersett, under Wymondham. Acres, 1, 428. Real property, £2, 743. Pop., 196. Houses, 25. The property is divided among a few. Hethel Thorn, near the church, is said to be as old as the time of King John. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £405. Patron, the Rev. J. H. Steward. The church is good, with a tower; and has a monument to Myles Branthwaite. There is a national school.. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
